1
00:00:11,167 --> 00:00:13,500
[tires rumbling]

2
00:00:13,583 --> 00:00:15,250
[engine rumbling]

3
00:00:19,647 --> 00:00:22,542
3 YEARS AGO

4
00:00:22,625 --> 00:00:24,458
[foreboding music playing]

5
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,458
[gravel crunching]

6
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:53,250
- [handbrake creaking]
- [music fades]

7
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:55,625
- [keys jangling]
- [lock rattling]

8
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:57,542
[door opens]

9
00:01:04,875 --> 00:01:06,833
[soft tense music playing]

10
00:01:06,917 --> 00:01:09,292
We're here. Get out.

11
00:01:18,167 --> 00:01:19,750
Line up over here.

12
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:25,708
Move.

13
00:01:25,792 --> 00:01:26,958
Keep moving.

14
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:29,167
Go.

15
00:01:30,458 --> 00:01:32,667
Boss, I'll take these two.

16
00:01:33,750 --> 00:01:35,292
- Hey!
- [henchman] Yes, sir.

17
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:37,708
Come on.

18
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:41,292
[grunts]

19
00:01:41,875 --> 00:01:43,708
[in Burmese] Where are you taking
my sisters?

20
00:01:43,792 --> 00:01:45,292
[worker in Thai] Stay still.

21
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:47,875
[in Burmese] That's my brother!
My brother!

22
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,042
[Seya] Let me go!

23
00:01:49,125 --> 00:01:50,958
- [music intensifies]
- We came here together.

24
00:01:51,042 --> 00:01:52,292
Seya!

25
00:01:52,375 --> 00:01:54,083
[grunting]

26
00:01:54,167 --> 00:01:55,167
[Seya] Nay Oo!

27
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:57,417
- [grunting]
- [Nay Oo and Nee An scream]

28
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:00,333
- [music concludes]
- [gunshot echoes]

29
00:02:00,417 --> 00:02:02,792
[high-pitched ringing]

30
00:02:03,917 --> 00:02:05,750
[Seya breathes shakily]

31
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:07,375
[soft tense music playing]

32
00:02:07,458 --> 00:02:10,792
[Chai in Thai] Rern, how many
will you put on the boat?

33
00:02:10,875 --> 00:02:11,875
[Rern] Ten.

34
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:14,750
[Chai] Take this piece of shit, too.

35
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,458
[Nay Oo sobs]

36
00:02:21,792 --> 00:02:23,333
[sobbing]

37
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,667
[music intensifies]

38
00:02:40,208 --> 00:02:42,250
[music falls]

39
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,417
[machinery whirring, clanking]

40
00:02:45,208 --> 00:02:47,167
[Chai] Why is the catch
so small this time?

41
00:02:48,417 --> 00:02:50,208
Maybe less than 50 tons.

42
00:02:51,042 --> 00:02:53,042
How many are missing?

43
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,708
[worker] Two, boss.

44
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:57,000
[Chai] And you're just telling me now?

45
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:01,042
When PIPO comes to inspect,
what the hell am I supposed to say?

46
00:03:01,667 --> 00:03:03,667
You better head back out right now. Go.

47
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,750
Or I'm docking all your pay.

48
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,167
[worker] Yes, boss.

49
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:09,458
- [workers shouting]
- [tense music continues]

50
00:03:31,875 --> 00:03:32,792
[lighter clicks]

51
00:03:33,667 --> 00:03:34,583
- [Seya grunts]
- [groans]

52
00:03:34,667 --> 00:03:35,875
[music rises]

53
00:03:37,458 --> 00:03:39,333
Where did you take my sister?

54
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:43,625
That cop.

55
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:45,625
He's working with you, isn't he?

56
00:03:46,875 --> 00:03:48,125
Where is my sister?

57
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:50,042
Just calm down.

58
00:03:51,292 --> 00:03:53,583
Which cop messed with you?
Tell me, I'll take care of it.

59
00:03:53,667 --> 00:03:55,417
Stop lying.

60
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,958
You're all in this together, right? Huh?

61
00:03:59,042 --> 00:04:00,667
Where did you take her?

62
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:04,458
Tell me or I'll shoot.

63
00:04:08,417 --> 00:04:11,417
Your sister?
Probably been fed to the fish by now.

64
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:13,375
[music rises]

65
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:14,458
[gun safety clicks]

66
00:04:14,542 --> 00:04:15,792
- [grunts]
- [Seya groans]

67
00:04:17,917 --> 00:04:18,917
[groans]

68
00:04:20,417 --> 00:04:22,208
- [Seya grunting]
- [music intensifies]

69
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,583
Think you're tough, bastard?

70
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:26,667
Think you're tough, huh?!

71
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,833
Don't even know how to take
the safety off, but you want to shoot me?

72
00:04:29,917 --> 00:04:31,250
[indistinct chatter]

73
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:32,708
[worker] Hey, boss!

74
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:36,125
- [heavy thud]
- Boss! Boss!

75
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,833
- Boss, that's enough!
- [grunting]

76
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:40,708
The workers are staring.

77
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:44,125
[grumbles]

78
00:04:45,208 --> 00:04:46,958
- [fast thud]
- Boss.

79
00:04:47,042 --> 00:04:48,375
Call the commander.

80
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,292
[panting]

81
00:04:54,375 --> 00:04:55,875
[worker] Hello, Commander?

82
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:59,583
A migrant tried to shoot Boss Chai.
Please send someone over.

83
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:02,167
- [panting]
- [music builds]

84
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:04,167
[music falls]

85
00:05:07,875 --> 00:05:10,208
THE EVIL LAWYER

86
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:12,167
[music concludes]

87
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:13,125
[button clicks]

88
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:16,208
[Jittri] Is this the defendant's
X-ray film?

89
00:05:16,292 --> 00:05:17,292
[Korn] Yes.

90
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,583
[Jittri] Is this the fractured collarbone?

91
00:05:19,667 --> 00:05:20,583
[Korn] Yes, it is.

92
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:23,875
Can a patient with this kind of fracture

93
00:05:23,958 --> 00:05:26,250
live a normal life after splinting?

94
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:28,042
[Korn] Yes, for the most part.

95
00:05:28,125 --> 00:05:31,292
But they shouldn't move their arm much
or lift heavy things as it'd cause pain.

96
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:34,250
How about a month after the fracture?

97
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,625
Is it possible they could use a golf club

98
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:38,292
to bash someone's skull in?

99
00:05:39,417 --> 00:05:41,167
In my opinion, it's impossible.

100
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,875
Typically, for an injury like this,

101
00:05:42,958 --> 00:05:45,292
it takes two to three months to heal.

102
00:05:45,875 --> 00:05:47,208
But it's only been a month.

103
00:05:47,292 --> 00:05:48,708
Even if he raises his arm,

104
00:05:48,792 --> 00:05:52,000
he wouldn't have the strength
to beat someone up anyway.

105
00:05:52,875 --> 00:05:54,000
[Noi] Hold on.

106
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:55,667
[soft intriguing music playing]

107
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:59,000
Why didn't the defendant
mention this injury

108
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:00,583
during his initial statement?

109
00:06:01,875 --> 00:06:05,208
The police never asked about any injuries.

110
00:06:05,292 --> 00:06:10,833
But you called a doctor,
who was charged with rape, as your witness

111
00:06:10,917 --> 00:06:13,917
and you were his lawyer for that case.

112
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,708
Isn't that a bit too coincidental?

113
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:22,375
I fear there might be collusion
to fabricate evidence after the fact.

114
00:06:22,458 --> 00:06:23,583
[Jittri] Objection.

115
00:06:23,667 --> 00:06:27,083
The prosecutor is bringing up another case
unrelated to this one.

116
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:28,083
[loud thud]

117
00:06:28,167 --> 00:06:30,750
Prosecutor, keep your questions
relevant to the case.

118
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:34,250
- [exciting music playing]
- Don't just mix different cases together.

119
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:36,750
Or I'll have your back caned to a pulp.

120
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:38,500
- [gong clashing]
- Wangchao, Mahan!

121
00:06:38,583 --> 00:06:39,583
[both] Yes, sir.

122
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:42,083
Bring forth the execution--

123
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:43,583
- Enough, you guys.
- [music stops]

124
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:46,042
It does seem too coincidental.

125
00:06:46,917 --> 00:06:49,500
Won't the judge think we're colluding?

126
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:52,000
[Jittri] Maybe, but so what?

127
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:54,958
The court's duty is to consider this case.

128
00:06:55,042 --> 00:06:58,333
They can't bring in other cases.
So you can relax.

129
00:06:59,917 --> 00:07:01,167
Okay, sounds good.

130
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:04,583
[Nemo] Ouch, Mom!

131
00:07:04,667 --> 00:07:06,500
[Kung speaking indistinctly]

132
00:07:06,583 --> 00:07:07,875
[Korn] Don't slouch.

133
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:10,292
Or the bone won't heal right.

134
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:11,875
- Okay?
- Okay.

135
00:07:12,458 --> 00:07:16,250
[indistinct chatter]

136
00:07:17,042 --> 00:07:18,458
Your pain won't be for nothing.

137
00:07:21,458 --> 00:07:25,125
[cell phone buzzing]

138
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:29,750
What is it, Ang?

139
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:32,500
THA KOH HOSPITAL

140
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:39,375
[Ang] The bullet didn't hit
any vital organs.

141
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:41,000
But Seya lost a lot of blood.

142
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,333
He was assaulted too.

143
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:46,417
So, the police let him rest
before the questioning.

144
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:51,083
The other side had filed a report first,
so Seya became the suspect.

145
00:07:56,708 --> 00:07:57,917
Seya.

146
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:00,708
Listen to me, Seya.

147
00:08:02,792 --> 00:08:06,833
The police will come back tomorrow
to ask you more questions.

148
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:10,708
But don't be afraid.

149
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:13,000
I'll be here with you.

150
00:08:14,125 --> 00:08:16,333
[medical device beeping]

151
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:20,167
I should've shot him dead.

152
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:27,583
He fucking killed Nee An.

153
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:32,125
And he took Nay Oo, too.

154
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,792
[soft sorrowful music playing]

155
00:08:36,875 --> 00:08:38,458
[sobs softly]

156
00:08:42,583 --> 00:08:43,625
[Mek] Seya.

157
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,792
Let me ask you something.

158
00:08:48,458 --> 00:08:50,000
Where did you get the gun?

159
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:55,208
[breathes shakily]

160
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:59,375
[insects trilling]

161
00:09:02,292 --> 00:09:06,083
[reporter speaking distinctly over TV]

162
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:09,042
[music fades]

163
00:09:11,917 --> 00:09:14,375
- [Noi] Jittri.
- Yes?

164
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:15,833
[Noi] Come here quickly!

165
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,708
Come here quickly, Jittri!

166
00:09:19,792 --> 00:09:22,083
[reporter] <i>…the scene</i>
<i>where a migrant worker</i>

167
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:24,500
<i>assaulted a local resident.</i>

168
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:27,125
<i>Our reporter went to the site to speak</i>

169
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:29,875
<i>with the injured victim</i>
<i>who owns the fishery.</i>

170
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:32,917
<i>- His name is Mr. Chaiwut Sinthornsuk.</i>
- [foreboding music playing]

171
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,167
<i>He stated he had never met</i>
<i>the attacker before</i>

172
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:39,250
<i>and suspected that</i>
<i>it was a case of mistaken identity.</i>

173
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:43,667
His face has changed a lot,
but his eyes are exactly the same.

174
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:46,208
[reporter continues indistinctly]

175
00:09:46,292 --> 00:09:49,625
[music rises, darkens]

176
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,417
[music builds]

177
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,750
[music stops]

178
00:09:57,667 --> 00:09:59,833
[soft tense music playing]

179
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:04,375
[music intensifies]

180
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:26,792
- [music fades]
- [high-pitched ringing]

181
00:10:27,375 --> 00:10:29,625
[muffled buzzing]

182
00:10:29,708 --> 00:10:30,625
[cell phone buzzing]

183
00:10:30,708 --> 00:10:32,583
[tense music resumes]

184
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:36,125
- Yeah?
- [Mek] <i>I found the missing gun.</i>

185
00:10:36,208 --> 00:10:38,250
<i>Nay Oo's brother used it</i>
<i>to shoot the fishery owner.</i>

186
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:40,833
<i>- I'm not sure if you saw the news.</i>
- We'll talk later.

187
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:47,833
[dark daring music playing]

188
00:10:52,917 --> 00:10:55,375
Hey, where are you going?
You can't go in there.

189
00:10:55,458 --> 00:10:56,542
[Jittri] Mr. Chaiwut.

190
00:10:58,250 --> 00:10:59,917
I'm Attorney Jittri.

191
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,708
I hear you're having legal trouble
that I can help with.

192
00:11:02,792 --> 00:11:05,333
[machinery whirring, clanking]

193
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,792
[workers chattering]

194
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,542
The famous lawyer. I've seen you on TV.

195
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:13,083
But I don't have any problems.

196
00:11:13,167 --> 00:11:14,792
I don't need a lawyer right now.

197
00:11:15,292 --> 00:11:18,083
Ah, you have
a powerful backer helping you.

198
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,792
Why waste money hiring a lawyer?

199
00:11:22,458 --> 00:11:24,833
But being too confident
isn't a good thing.

200
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:28,500
It will eventually backfire on you.

201
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:32,208
I'll just leave my card with you.

202
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:35,208
Just in case
you ever need my services one day.

203
00:11:38,083 --> 00:11:39,958
[music fades]

204
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:47,125
[Jittri] That's a nasty scar.

205
00:11:47,208 --> 00:11:48,375
What happened to you?

206
00:11:48,917 --> 00:11:50,625
[soft tense music playing]

207
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:52,875
A dog bit me. Why do you ask?

208
00:11:54,292 --> 00:11:58,292
You must have really pissed it off.
It bit you quite hard.

209
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:04,958
Contact me if you need help.

210
00:12:05,042 --> 00:12:07,917
For you, I'll offer a special rate.

211
00:12:11,292 --> 00:12:13,250
[music rises]

212
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:22,583
SERGEANT YUTTHACHAI KOMPACHARA

213
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:26,500
[Chanon] His old name was Yutthachai.
He left the force in '92.

214
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:28,708
- Right after the Ban Mae Tawo case.
- [music fades]

215
00:12:28,792 --> 00:12:30,542
[Chanon] After that,
he completely vanished

216
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:32,792
and showed up again in 2013.

217
00:12:32,875 --> 00:12:34,917
He's been running
the local fish markets ever since.

218
00:12:37,458 --> 00:12:39,750
This guy's been with Anan
for a very long time.

219
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:42,792
Are you sure you can get him on our side?

220
00:12:44,208 --> 00:12:45,542
A drowning man

221
00:12:46,042 --> 00:12:48,083
will always do what it takes to survive.

222
00:12:51,875 --> 00:12:55,500
The gun the boy used to shoot Chai
is Anan's, just like you said.

223
00:12:57,792 --> 00:12:59,792
Here's the evidence and gun registration.

224
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:01,792
That was fast.

225
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:08,000
Will you tell me about yourself now?

226
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:11,333
Why the sudden interest in my life?

227
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:12,750
[Chanon chuckles]

228
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:16,292
[sighs]

229
00:13:16,375 --> 00:13:17,958
EVIDENCE:
MIGRANT WORKER ASSAULTS EMPLOYER

230
00:13:18,625 --> 00:13:20,208
Don't you want to know about me?

231
00:13:21,583 --> 00:13:23,083
I already know everything I need.

232
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,917
[Chanon] I'm divorced now.

233
00:13:39,958 --> 00:13:41,417
I told you…

234
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,875
that I'd show you just how serious I am.

235
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:49,417
My wife took the kid,
so I've given her the house.

236
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:53,292
This little guy is all I have left.

237
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:58,583
But it's fine. I get to start--

238
00:13:58,667 --> 00:14:00,958
I made our boundaries very clear
from day one.

239
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:06,083
Do whatever you want with your life.
No need to tell me.

240
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:09,917
I've always been clear on my limits.

241
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,000
Is that enough? Or is it too little?

242
00:14:12,083 --> 00:14:13,458
Only you can answer that.

243
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,000
Thanks for this.

244
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:21,542
[pensive music playing]

245
00:14:26,042 --> 00:14:27,292
[inhales deeply]

246
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:28,625
[sighs]

247
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:32,417
[meows]

248
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:35,208
[chuckles softly]

249
00:14:46,208 --> 00:14:49,458
[Kung] Have you posted
the gun details on Facebook?

250
00:14:49,542 --> 00:14:50,542
[music fades]

251
00:14:50,625 --> 00:14:51,667
How's it looking?

252
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,583
All done. I'm about to post it now.

253
00:14:54,917 --> 00:14:58,208
HOW DID A POLICE GUN END UP
WITH A BURMESE WORKER?

254
00:14:58,292 --> 00:15:01,167
Damn it! Are you writing a research paper?

255
00:15:01,250 --> 00:15:03,375
Who's gonna share this crap, idiot?

256
00:15:03,458 --> 00:15:05,500
Move. We'll handle this ourselves.

257
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:07,167
Hey, kid, is the setup ready?

258
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,375
- [electric buzz]
- [in English] Let's go, my brother!

259
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:11,250
[suspenseful music builds]

260
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:12,792
- [music stops]
- [echoing rumble]

261
00:15:14,375 --> 00:15:17,000
[energetic electronic music playing]

262
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,667
Ready, set, and…

263
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:21,667
- [music stops]
- [computer chimes]

264
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:24,333
SCANDAL: TOP COP PLANTS GUN ON MIGRANT

265
00:15:24,417 --> 00:15:25,375
[music resumes]

266
00:15:25,458 --> 00:15:27,958
FISH MARKET BOSS ALMOST KILLED

267
00:15:28,042 --> 00:15:28,917
[music stops]

268
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,208
[computer chirping]

269
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:32,083
NEED THE GUN OWNER'S NAME ASAP

270
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:33,083
[Kung] …go!

271
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:35,083
- [music resumes]
- [computer chiming rapidly]

272
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:40,208
100% POLICE WEAPON.
GUN LOVERS GROUP CONFIRMS.

273
00:15:40,292 --> 00:15:41,708
DID THE COP HIRE THE MIGRANT?

274
00:15:41,792 --> 00:15:43,167
CHECK THE REGISTRATION FOR OWNER.

275
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:47,417
[computer chirping, chiming]

276
00:15:56,375 --> 00:15:57,667
SCANDAL OVER LEAKED WEAPON!

277
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:01,167
[Kung in Thai] Selling like hot cakes.

278
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:02,375
Pow!

279
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:03,958
Bam!

280
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,000
Boom!

281
00:16:06,792 --> 00:16:09,083
[Kung] What a mess!

282
00:16:09,167 --> 00:16:11,958
- [laughing]
- [computer chiming]

283
00:16:12,042 --> 00:16:14,792
[Kung] We go all out, baby!

284
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:17,917
Absolutely no holds barred!

285
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,167
[group exclaiming]

286
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:21,292
GRABBING POPCORN.
TOP COP'S NAME DROPS TONIGHT!

287
00:16:21,375 --> 00:16:24,333
[scanner whirring]

288
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:27,667
FIREARM LICENSE

289
00:16:28,542 --> 00:16:30,875
FIREARM OWNER:
POL. GEN. ANAN METHANEEPAISAL

290
00:16:30,958 --> 00:16:33,000
[Kung] Locked and loaded.

291
00:16:34,708 --> 00:16:37,167
[in English] See you in hell,
my friend, bro!

292
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:40,125
- [echoing thud]
- [news theme music playing]

293
00:16:40,208 --> 00:16:43,000
TRENDING NEWS

294
00:16:47,458 --> 00:16:50,750
[in Thai] Hello.
I'm here with the top stories

295
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,375
for February 19, 2026.

296
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:55,667
The issue making waves
online right now

297
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:58,625
is an anonymous leak of evidence

298
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:01,000
showing the gun used in the crime

299
00:17:01,083 --> 00:17:02,792
involving a migrant worker

300
00:17:02,875 --> 00:17:06,333
attacking a fishery owner
in the Tha Koh Community.

301
00:17:06,417 --> 00:17:08,292
According to the data and evidence,

302
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:10,708
the real owner of the gun

303
00:17:10,792 --> 00:17:13,208
is Police General Anan Methaneepaisal,

304
00:17:13,292 --> 00:17:14,292
also known as Big Anan.

305
00:17:14,375 --> 00:17:16,292
- [foreboding music playing]
- Many are now asking,

306
00:17:16,375 --> 00:17:20,250
how did Big Anan's gun end up
in the hands of a migrant worker?

307
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:22,458
Let's hear his response.

308
00:17:22,542 --> 00:17:25,583
[reporter] The culprit used your gun
to shoot the fishery owner.

309
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:28,625
Did you know the owner's a former cop?

310
00:17:29,958 --> 00:17:32,208
I don't think that's relevant to the case.

311
00:17:32,708 --> 00:17:36,250
The only fact is that my gun
was stolen and used in a crime.

312
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:41,125
But the victim is Mr. Chaiwut Sinthornsuk.
Isn't he your former subordinate?

313
00:17:44,083 --> 00:17:45,083
[sighs]

314
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:46,708
I've been a cop my whole life.

315
00:17:47,583 --> 00:17:50,792
I've commanded countless officers.

316
00:17:50,875 --> 00:17:53,458
I can't possibly remember all their names.

317
00:17:53,542 --> 00:17:54,542
Excuse me.

318
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:56,875
- Sir!
- Sir, we need more explanation!

319
00:17:56,958 --> 00:17:58,000
Please don't go yet, sir!

320
00:17:58,083 --> 00:18:00,500
- [clock ticking]
- [reporter] Don't go! You need to explain!

321
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:02,083
- Sir! Sir!
- [muffled chatter]

322
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:06,333
<i>Moving on to the migrant worker</i>
<i>who attacked the fishery owner,</i>

323
00:18:06,417 --> 00:18:10,542
<i>our sources confirm that</i>
<i>the fishery owner, Chai,</i>

324
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:12,458
<i>or Mr. Chaiwut Sinthornsuk,</i>

325
00:18:12,542 --> 00:18:15,167
<i>is a former subordinate of General Anan</i>

326
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:18,083
<i>- from his time stationed in Tak province.</i>
- [dark pensive music playing]

327
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:20,125
[reporter] <i>And the photo you see right now</i>

328
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:22,333
<i>is the one being shared online.</i>

329
00:18:22,417 --> 00:18:24,250
<i>It shows that the two were close.</i>

330
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,542
CRIMINAL CASE 1992

331
00:18:27,625 --> 00:18:29,583
[clock ticking continues]

332
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:31,292
[music rises]

333
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:43,000
[music fades]

334
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:46,792
[machinery clunking, whirring]

335
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:53,750
[heavy clunk]

336
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:03,042
[worker] Boss! The cops are here!

337
00:19:03,125 --> 00:19:05,500
[soft tense music playing]

338
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:09,333
[indistinct chatter]

339
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:14,208
[Chai] What's going on?

340
00:19:18,667 --> 00:19:19,875
[officer 1] Search warrant.

341
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:23,375
I heard your boats have been
finding rare items lately.

342
00:19:23,458 --> 00:19:25,125
I need to take a look around.

343
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:28,542
Who's your boss? I've never seen you.

344
00:19:29,792 --> 00:19:31,542
I don't work for anyone.

345
00:19:31,625 --> 00:19:34,250
Someone tipped us off,
so I came to search.

346
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:36,042
It's nothing personal.

347
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:37,125
[Chai] Who?

348
00:19:37,208 --> 00:19:39,417
Who the fuck gave you the lead? Tell me!

349
00:19:39,917 --> 00:19:42,958
My boats only carry fish.
There's no illegal shit here.

350
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:45,583
And if you don't find anything…

351
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:47,000
I'm coming for you.

352
00:19:47,083 --> 00:19:48,708
[officer 2] Found it! It's crystal meth!

353
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:51,917
Lieutenant, come help me search.

354
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,583
Only carry fish?

355
00:19:56,875 --> 00:19:59,667
Looks like we have a lot to discuss.

356
00:20:03,708 --> 00:20:04,708
[officer 3] Excuse me.

357
00:20:04,792 --> 00:20:05,917
[handcuffs jangling]

358
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:08,458
[handcuffs creak, click]

359
00:20:08,542 --> 00:20:12,167
[cell phone buzzing]

360
00:20:12,917 --> 00:20:14,167
[Anan sniffs]

361
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:19,292
[sighs]

362
00:20:20,125 --> 00:20:22,125
[music fades]

363
00:20:23,708 --> 00:20:24,667
[officer 1 scoffs]

364
00:20:25,208 --> 00:20:26,250
[officer 1] Hey.

365
00:20:27,542 --> 00:20:28,958
Who else will you call?

366
00:20:40,875 --> 00:20:42,125
Tell me the truth.

367
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:44,292
Who's behind this?

368
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:46,708
How long have you run this fishery?

369
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:51,625
You answer me first.

370
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:53,667
Who put you up to this?

371
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:56,750
Where did the drugs come from,
and where are they going?

372
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:07,375
If you refuse to cooperate,

373
00:21:08,458 --> 00:21:10,167
I'll have my guys search your house

374
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:13,708
and that might get your family in trouble.

375
00:21:14,375 --> 00:21:16,792
[foreboding music playing]

376
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:19,708
Your daughter…

377
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:22,417
Maysa.

378
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:25,500
She's still so little.

379
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,292
I want a lawyer.

380
00:21:42,292 --> 00:21:43,417
Mm.

381
00:21:45,792 --> 00:21:47,542
[music fades]

382
00:21:48,292 --> 00:21:49,875
We meet again sooner than I expected.

383
00:21:52,708 --> 00:21:55,542
Who did you piss off
to get framed for drug trafficking?

384
00:21:58,792 --> 00:22:00,292
But you picked the right lawyer.

385
00:22:00,917 --> 00:22:03,375
Not many would risk their reputation

386
00:22:03,458 --> 00:22:05,292
on a major drug trafficking suspect.

387
00:22:05,375 --> 00:22:06,792
I've never had issues with anyone.

388
00:22:06,875 --> 00:22:09,708
That doesn't mean
they don't have a problem with you.

389
00:22:10,542 --> 00:22:12,375
There's massive money in fisheries.

390
00:22:12,458 --> 00:22:15,917
If your market, one of the biggest,
suddenly went under,

391
00:22:16,542 --> 00:22:18,667
everyone else would get a bigger cut.

392
00:22:21,292 --> 00:22:24,417
Listen, if you want to beat this case,

393
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:26,250
do exactly as I say.

394
00:22:28,417 --> 00:22:29,583
I'm listening.

395
00:22:30,458 --> 00:22:31,875
[tense music playing]

396
00:22:31,958 --> 00:22:35,083
Whoever set you up probably knows
the exact locations of your fleet.

397
00:22:36,625 --> 00:22:38,458
Give me the coordinates of every ship.

398
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:41,250
And hide the illegal workers for now.

399
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:44,292
I'll handle the legal side.

400
00:22:44,375 --> 00:22:45,833
[music fades]

401
00:22:51,542 --> 00:22:54,833
And keep my wife and daughter out of this.

402
00:22:57,125 --> 00:22:58,750
Even your big backer can't help?

403
00:22:58,833 --> 00:23:00,417
[tense music resumes]

404
00:23:03,167 --> 00:23:04,750
He's probably busy.

405
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:09,292
Are you sure you didn't do anything
to piss him off?

406
00:23:12,750 --> 00:23:14,292
I've seen it too many times.

407
00:23:14,375 --> 00:23:17,708
Powerful people are always
ready to discard little guys like us.

408
00:23:18,625 --> 00:23:19,917
[music fades]

409
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,375
But don't worry.

410
00:23:21,458 --> 00:23:24,042
I gave you my word. I'll do my best.

411
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:28,625
If little guys like us
don't help each other,

412
00:23:28,708 --> 00:23:31,000
who will? Right?

413
00:23:32,917 --> 00:23:35,250
[dark tense music playing]

414
00:23:42,458 --> 00:23:44,083
[music builds]

415
00:23:44,750 --> 00:23:45,875
[music concludes]

416
00:23:45,958 --> 00:23:49,500
[officer 1] Whoa!
Look at the crazy cat lover.

417
00:23:50,083 --> 00:23:51,667
- Oh.
- [music concludes]

418
00:23:52,292 --> 00:23:53,458
Thanks so much, Ju.

419
00:23:53,542 --> 00:23:55,083
- All set?
- [Jittri] Uh-huh.

420
00:23:55,167 --> 00:23:56,917
- [Ju] See you later.
- See you, bro.

421
00:24:02,875 --> 00:24:03,958
Wait.

422
00:24:08,042 --> 00:24:09,333
I'm sorry.

423
00:24:23,542 --> 00:24:24,750
How did it go?

424
00:24:24,833 --> 00:24:27,625
He's starting to suspect Anan
planted the drugs to take him out.

425
00:24:29,375 --> 00:24:31,208
I never thought your plan would work.

426
00:24:31,708 --> 00:24:34,000
Turning people against each other is easy.

427
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:38,542
[sighs]

428
00:24:40,292 --> 00:24:42,292
But I can't wait for you to turn me on.

429
00:24:44,083 --> 00:24:45,167
Just drive.

430
00:24:50,250 --> 00:24:52,250
[soft tense music playing]

431
00:24:56,125 --> 00:24:58,708
- [insects trilling]
- [car horn honking]

432
00:25:00,625 --> 00:25:02,500
[music fades]

433
00:25:06,708 --> 00:25:07,750
[Rit] Mek.

434
00:25:11,417 --> 00:25:12,625
What is it?

435
00:25:13,667 --> 00:25:14,625
[sighs]

436
00:25:15,333 --> 00:25:16,375
Can we talk?

437
00:25:17,042 --> 00:25:18,958
I have something important to tell you.

438
00:25:20,250 --> 00:25:22,417
- [Mek] Listen, today I--
- It's about Jittri.

439
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:36,083
[insects trilling]

440
00:25:36,167 --> 00:25:38,333
I met her when she was a kid.

441
00:25:40,375 --> 00:25:43,250
Not just Jittri, but her mother too.

442
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:48,750
Her mother once filed a complaint

443
00:25:48,833 --> 00:25:51,833
stating that her husband
had been accused of human trafficking

444
00:25:51,917 --> 00:25:53,542
and that he was later abducted.

445
00:25:55,042 --> 00:25:56,292
[soft tense music playing]

446
00:25:56,375 --> 00:25:59,417
[Rit]
The local police refused to file a case

447
00:26:00,708 --> 00:26:02,625
because they feared the local bosses.

448
00:26:03,833 --> 00:26:05,250
So she built the case herself…

449
00:26:07,042 --> 00:26:09,125
and submitted it
to the Bangkok Criminal Court.

450
00:26:12,250 --> 00:26:14,500
The chief forwarded it to me to review.

451
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,708
Why didn't you accept her case?

452
00:26:22,792 --> 00:26:26,583
There was no evidence
for her claim about his abduction.

453
00:26:28,417 --> 00:26:31,458
And looking at the police report,
it's highly possible that

454
00:26:31,542 --> 00:26:34,375
her husband simply fled
to avoid arrest.

455
00:26:43,208 --> 00:26:46,917
I wonder if Jittri still holds a grudge
about me dismissing her dad's case.

456
00:26:52,833 --> 00:26:54,292
I might be overthinking it.

457
00:26:56,250 --> 00:26:57,917
But you should stay on your guard.

458
00:27:00,125 --> 00:27:03,875
Because we have no idea
what she really wants.

459
00:27:12,083 --> 00:27:13,833
[tense music continues]

460
00:27:19,083 --> 00:27:21,083
[brush scratching]

461
00:27:22,333 --> 00:27:25,583
[cell phone buzzing]

462
00:27:31,167 --> 00:27:33,667
- What is it?
- [man] <i>Chai just got arrested, boss.</i>

463
00:27:34,708 --> 00:27:36,125
Arrested for what?

464
00:27:36,208 --> 00:27:38,333
[man] <i>They found meth in his cold storage.</i>

465
00:27:38,917 --> 00:27:41,000
<i>Jittri was the one who bailed him out.</i>

466
00:27:41,083 --> 00:27:41,958
Huh…

467
00:27:42,042 --> 00:27:43,625
- [knocking on door]
- [door opens]

468
00:27:45,625 --> 00:27:47,583
Attorney Jittri is here to see you, sir.

469
00:27:47,667 --> 00:27:49,292
[music rises]

470
00:27:49,375 --> 00:27:51,625
[music concludes]

471
00:28:03,083 --> 00:28:05,042
[Anan] Are you interested
in these things too?

472
00:28:09,542 --> 00:28:12,083
They're interesting as an investment.

473
00:28:14,500 --> 00:28:16,917
But not for worship.

474
00:28:18,167 --> 00:28:21,250
I don't have faith in the abstract
or the intangible.

475
00:28:21,333 --> 00:28:22,458
[chuckles softly]

476
00:28:22,542 --> 00:28:25,333
You're a lawyer fighting for justice.

477
00:28:26,042 --> 00:28:28,083
Isn't that an abstract concept too?

478
00:28:29,833 --> 00:28:31,458
But I don't have faith in justice.

479
00:28:31,542 --> 00:28:33,625
[chuckles] You don't…

480
00:28:34,625 --> 00:28:36,042
because of your past?

481
00:28:37,375 --> 00:28:41,125
If you mean our past, then perhaps.

482
00:28:43,167 --> 00:28:45,792
But I came here to inform you

483
00:28:45,875 --> 00:28:50,083
that I am now representing Mr. Chaiwut,
your close subordinate.

484
00:28:50,792 --> 00:28:54,458
I'm sure you know he was arrested
for drug smuggling.

485
00:28:55,708 --> 00:28:58,500
As a lawyer, I need to know

486
00:28:58,583 --> 00:29:02,167
what other businesses
my client is involved in.

487
00:29:05,333 --> 00:29:07,583
People can be terrifying when cornered.

488
00:29:09,458 --> 00:29:11,875
- Those once loyal…
- [tense music playing]

489
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:14,667
…can just as easily betray you
in order to survive.

490
00:29:17,958 --> 00:29:21,042
The coordinates of all your ships,
both registered and unregistered.

491
00:29:22,667 --> 00:29:24,833
Ownership transfer documents.

492
00:29:26,042 --> 00:29:28,458
Evidence of duplicate shipping licenses.

493
00:29:30,125 --> 00:29:31,750
Forged work permits.

494
00:29:32,458 --> 00:29:36,042
Fishing boats, fish markets… What else?

495
00:29:39,042 --> 00:29:41,583
Human trafficking, how's that?

496
00:29:41,667 --> 00:29:42,625
[music rises]

497
00:29:42,708 --> 00:29:45,042
[Jittri] You have money,
strong backing, and influence.

498
00:29:45,125 --> 00:29:48,083
But these days,
information is the ultimate weapon.

499
00:29:49,083 --> 00:29:51,792
No one knows
when it might suddenly explode.

500
00:29:52,917 --> 00:29:54,875
And the thing about an explosion

501
00:29:54,958 --> 00:29:58,542
is that you can't control
who gets caught in the blast.

502
00:30:02,458 --> 00:30:03,708
What do you want?

503
00:30:05,708 --> 00:30:07,167
I don't really want anything.

504
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,375
I just want to help Mek beat his case.

505
00:30:11,250 --> 00:30:13,083
Helping out a fellow human being

506
00:30:13,167 --> 00:30:15,333
is the right thing to do, isn't it?

507
00:30:18,333 --> 00:30:19,417
[sighs]

508
00:30:34,458 --> 00:30:36,667
You must have wondered your whole life

509
00:30:36,750 --> 00:30:38,625
about what happened to your father.

510
00:30:41,958 --> 00:30:43,458
And the fact that you…

511
00:30:44,750 --> 00:30:47,708
are defending the murderer
who killed my son…

512
00:30:48,875 --> 00:30:51,250
[chuckles] …and threatening me
in my own home…

513
00:30:54,375 --> 00:30:56,000
proves you just want answers

514
00:30:56,625 --> 00:30:58,208
about your father.

515
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:05,958
[music turns ominous]

516
00:31:13,667 --> 00:31:15,917
I'll give you some time to think it over.

517
00:31:17,333 --> 00:31:18,500
But don't forget…

518
00:31:19,292 --> 00:31:21,625
not every cop is loyal to you.

519
00:31:22,625 --> 00:31:24,083
Last I heard,

520
00:31:24,792 --> 00:31:27,625
someone is issuing search warrants
for all your ships.

521
00:31:29,958 --> 00:31:32,167
But whether it actually comes to that…

522
00:31:33,917 --> 00:31:35,625
is entirely up to you.

523
00:31:41,458 --> 00:31:43,500
[music intensifies]

524
00:31:55,125 --> 00:31:57,083
[music concludes]

525
00:31:59,250 --> 00:32:01,917
[Jittri] We need to handle
Chai's drug case first.

526
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,833
He was caught red-handed.

527
00:32:03,917 --> 00:32:06,958
If we want him to walk,
we have to spin a new story.

528
00:32:08,750 --> 00:32:12,208
Wait, I don't get it. Why involve Chai?

529
00:32:12,292 --> 00:32:14,708
The gun is already linked to Anan.

530
00:32:15,917 --> 00:32:18,375
We need Chai to be our witness.

531
00:32:18,458 --> 00:32:20,875
He knows everything
about Anan's operations.

532
00:32:20,958 --> 00:32:23,375
He has proof that
Anan is trafficking humans.

533
00:32:24,083 --> 00:32:26,500
The Burmese siblings
you're looking for do exist,

534
00:32:26,583 --> 00:32:27,625
and they're Anan's victims.

535
00:32:30,458 --> 00:32:32,417
I thought you said
you wouldn't go this route.

536
00:32:34,708 --> 00:32:37,917
Things have changed.
We need to have a few options.

537
00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:40,625
[Kung] How do we get Chai
off the hook, boss?

538
00:32:41,833 --> 00:32:44,833
With a drug bust this big,
the DA has to indict him.

539
00:32:46,250 --> 00:32:48,042
The sentence is prison either way.

540
00:32:48,792 --> 00:32:50,542
But Chai won't be in jail.

541
00:32:52,708 --> 00:32:53,833
This is Leh.

542
00:32:53,917 --> 00:32:56,708
A Thai worker trafficked onto a boat
for several years.

543
00:32:56,792 --> 00:32:58,833
He'll be the one going to jail
for this.

544
00:32:58,917 --> 00:33:01,708
- [tense music playing]
- You'll use a scapegoat?

545
00:33:03,917 --> 00:33:05,917
In a massive drug case like this,

546
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,792
the only way out is finding a fall guy.

547
00:33:08,875 --> 00:33:09,917
I'm out then.

548
00:33:10,958 --> 00:33:12,542
I'm fighting to avoid being a scapegoat.

549
00:33:13,292 --> 00:33:15,250
And now you want me to frame this guy?

550
00:33:15,333 --> 00:33:17,250
What kind of an asshole
would that make me?

551
00:33:17,333 --> 00:33:19,750
[Jittri] You don't make
the decisions. I do.

552
00:33:19,833 --> 00:33:21,417
- Are we done?
- [Mek] No, we're not.

553
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:23,250
Like hell we're done.

554
00:33:23,333 --> 00:33:24,958
[Jittri] If we don't get Chai to testify,

555
00:33:25,042 --> 00:33:28,083
we can't prove a third party
was involved in your case.

556
00:33:28,167 --> 00:33:31,208
[Mek] And what makes you so sure
that Chai will agree to testify?

557
00:33:31,292 --> 00:33:33,917
If Anan goes down for human trafficking,
he'll go down with him.

558
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:35,542
Right? You said it yourself

559
00:33:35,625 --> 00:33:37,875
that Chai has always been
Anan's right-hand man.

560
00:33:38,500 --> 00:33:41,250
I can drop his charges down
to just forced labor.

561
00:33:41,333 --> 00:33:43,167
Chai is just a subordinate anyway.

562
00:33:43,250 --> 00:33:45,625
The penalty for that is far lighter
than for drug trafficking.

563
00:33:45,708 --> 00:33:47,208
Which do you think he'll choose?

564
00:33:50,917 --> 00:33:53,292
Listen, Leh decided to do this.

565
00:33:53,375 --> 00:33:54,750
He has his own reasons.

566
00:33:54,833 --> 00:33:56,875
Don't worry about him.
He made his own decision.

567
00:33:57,500 --> 00:33:59,583
And we'll compensate him as best we can.

568
00:34:00,458 --> 00:34:01,417
[soft thud]

569
00:34:03,417 --> 00:34:04,583
[Jittri] Let's continue, Noi.

570
00:34:07,292 --> 00:34:09,500
[tense music continues]

571
00:34:11,250 --> 00:34:13,042
[shredder whirring]

572
00:34:20,083 --> 00:34:22,583
- [whirring stops]
- [cell phone buzzing]

573
00:34:27,125 --> 00:34:28,792
- Hey.
- [music fades]

574
00:34:28,875 --> 00:34:31,125
<i>Daddy, when are you coming home?</i>

575
00:34:31,208 --> 00:34:33,583
Hmm… My sweet Maysa.

576
00:34:33,667 --> 00:34:36,333
You're still awake, sweetie?
It's getting late.

577
00:34:36,417 --> 00:34:40,667
<i>Scold her, Daddy.</i>
<i>I told her to sleep but she won't listen.</i>

578
00:34:40,750 --> 00:34:42,500
<i>She says she's waiting for you.</i>

579
00:34:42,583 --> 00:34:44,125
Don't wait up for me, sweetie.

580
00:34:44,208 --> 00:34:45,708
Go ahead and get some sleep.

581
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:48,208
Hug Moo Daeng and give her a kiss for me.

582
00:34:48,292 --> 00:34:51,792
I'll kiss you myself when I get home.

583
00:34:52,292 --> 00:34:54,458
- Go to sleep, sweetie.
- [Maysa] <i>Yes, Daddy.</i>

584
00:34:55,167 --> 00:34:57,917
[Chai] Mommy,
is the guard I sent still there?

585
00:34:58,458 --> 00:35:00,708
<i>Yeah, he's right outside the house.</i>

586
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:04,208
Good. I'll hurry back.

587
00:35:04,292 --> 00:35:06,292
[Kaewta] <i>Maysa, say bye-bye to Daddy.</i>

588
00:35:06,375 --> 00:35:08,208
[in English] Bye, bye. Bye, bye.

589
00:35:09,125 --> 00:35:10,417
[in Thai] <i>Blow him a kiss.</i>

590
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:11,792
Bye-bye. Mwah!

591
00:35:13,833 --> 00:35:14,833
[cell phone beeps]

592
00:35:17,167 --> 00:35:18,333
[Chai] Pui!

593
00:35:21,583 --> 00:35:23,458
Get the truck ready. I'm heading out.

594
00:35:34,917 --> 00:35:37,333
[thunder rumbling]

595
00:35:39,458 --> 00:35:41,000
[engine rumbling]

596
00:35:54,458 --> 00:35:56,417
[thunder rumbles]

597
00:36:08,750 --> 00:36:10,042
Where the hell is everyone?

598
00:36:11,750 --> 00:36:13,250
[thunder crashes]

599
00:36:19,708 --> 00:36:20,708
[sinister music playing]

600
00:36:20,792 --> 00:36:21,750
[Chai] Hey!

601
00:36:24,583 --> 00:36:27,083
[groans]

602
00:36:29,458 --> 00:36:31,000
[groaning]

603
00:36:33,250 --> 00:36:35,000
[music intensifies]

604
00:36:40,167 --> 00:36:41,667
[Chai groans]

605
00:36:42,458 --> 00:36:44,125
[breathing heavily]

606
00:36:46,625 --> 00:36:48,083
[groans]

607
00:36:50,542 --> 00:36:52,708
[grunts, chokes]

608
00:36:55,500 --> 00:36:56,458
[grunts]

609
00:36:59,125 --> 00:37:01,458
[forklift whirring]

610
00:37:06,667 --> 00:37:09,875
[chokes, groans]

611
00:37:14,375 --> 00:37:16,625
[chain jangling]

612
00:37:19,167 --> 00:37:20,625
[gasps, chokes]

613
00:37:21,875 --> 00:37:23,958
[grunting]

614
00:37:25,750 --> 00:37:27,042
- [choking]
- [music builds]

615
00:37:27,667 --> 00:37:28,750
- [gunshot]
- [clank]

616
00:37:29,625 --> 00:37:30,667
[gunshot]

617
00:37:30,750 --> 00:37:33,250
- [music fades]
- [Chai groaning]

618
00:37:34,750 --> 00:37:37,333
[Chai choking]

619
00:37:39,708 --> 00:37:42,167
- [engine revving]
- [tires screeching]

620
00:37:43,583 --> 00:37:45,708
[intense music playing]

621
00:37:46,667 --> 00:37:49,000
[choking]

622
00:37:52,917 --> 00:37:53,958
[forklift clanks]

623
00:37:56,958 --> 00:37:58,458
[panting]

624
00:37:59,375 --> 00:38:02,042
[groans, coughs]

625
00:38:04,375 --> 00:38:07,208
- [chain jangling]
- [Chai wheezing]

626
00:38:10,292 --> 00:38:11,875
[coughs]

627
00:38:15,250 --> 00:38:17,208
[music falls]

628
00:38:41,375 --> 00:38:42,458
Did you already know…

629
00:38:43,250 --> 00:38:45,667
- that someone was coming to kill me?
- [music fades]

630
00:38:45,750 --> 00:38:48,917
[Jittri] The person behind this
always meant to silence you.

631
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:51,167
I just sent my people to watch your back.

632
00:38:56,583 --> 00:38:57,958
I know who did this.

633
00:38:58,042 --> 00:39:00,208
I want this over as soon as possible.

634
00:39:00,292 --> 00:39:01,625
You can handle it, right?

635
00:39:01,708 --> 00:39:03,125
[Jittri] I can definitely handle it.

636
00:39:03,667 --> 00:39:05,792
But I don't think
you're telling me the whole truth.

637
00:39:08,167 --> 00:39:11,167
The guy who tried to take me out is Anan.

638
00:39:11,750 --> 00:39:14,833
He might've planted the drugs on me
to keep me quiet about the gun.

639
00:39:16,375 --> 00:39:18,750
You need to clear this case fast.

640
00:39:18,833 --> 00:39:21,208
I'm taking my family out of the country.

641
00:39:22,708 --> 00:39:23,833
What do you want?

642
00:39:24,375 --> 00:39:26,583
Cash, gold? Just name it.

643
00:39:26,667 --> 00:39:28,250
I don't want your money.

644
00:39:29,250 --> 00:39:31,417
I'd rather hear the truth from you.

645
00:39:32,042 --> 00:39:33,458
I'm already going to testify.

646
00:39:33,542 --> 00:39:34,958
[Jittri] Not for this case.

647
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:40,458
The 1992 Ban Mae Tawo disappearance case.

648
00:39:41,125 --> 00:39:42,875
What happened to the ferry driver?

649
00:39:42,958 --> 00:39:45,333
[tense music playing]

650
00:39:48,125 --> 00:39:50,292
That case is over 30 years old.

651
00:39:51,708 --> 00:39:53,292
The statute of limitations has expired.

652
00:39:53,375 --> 00:39:55,125
What more do you want from me?

653
00:39:55,208 --> 00:39:56,667
What did you do to him?

654
00:40:03,208 --> 00:40:05,375
[music rises]

655
00:40:05,458 --> 00:40:07,042
[Chai] Argh!

656
00:40:07,125 --> 00:40:10,042
[Chai screaming]

657
00:40:10,125 --> 00:40:12,292
Let go of me, you little shit!

658
00:40:18,417 --> 00:40:21,000
- Daddy!
- Muleng!

659
00:40:21,083 --> 00:40:22,417
[in Shan] Go home!

660
00:40:22,542 --> 00:40:25,167
- [young Jittri] Daddy!
- Go home!

661
00:40:25,250 --> 00:40:27,375
- [young Jittri] Daddy!
- [Jai in Shan] Go!

662
00:40:28,500 --> 00:40:30,000
- Go!
- [young Jittri in Thai] Daddy!

663
00:40:33,208 --> 00:40:34,917
[music falls]

664
00:40:35,750 --> 00:40:37,167
You're that little girl?

665
00:40:37,792 --> 00:40:40,125
[music rises, darkens]

666
00:40:44,333 --> 00:40:47,000
Your dad is dead.
What more do you want to know?

667
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:49,917
Why did you kill him?

668
00:40:51,167 --> 00:40:52,375
I didn't do it.

669
00:40:54,292 --> 00:40:55,750
Where did you put my father's body?

670
00:40:59,583 --> 00:41:02,417
Get the drug charges against me
dropped first.

671
00:41:03,625 --> 00:41:06,083
Then, I'll take you right to him.

672
00:41:06,167 --> 00:41:08,167
[music intensifies]

673
00:41:13,167 --> 00:41:14,750
[music concludes]

674
00:41:14,833 --> 00:41:17,417
[Mek] Let's go over this again.
Where did the drugs come from?

675
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:20,042
[Leh] They came from the border by car.

676
00:41:20,125 --> 00:41:21,750
Then they were kept in cold storage.

677
00:41:21,833 --> 00:41:23,667
[Mek] Did anyone else know about this?

678
00:41:23,750 --> 00:41:26,667
No one besides me and the users.

679
00:41:27,833 --> 00:41:32,250
- [Mek] And the users on the boat…
- Only they and I knew about it.

680
00:41:32,333 --> 00:41:34,125
The captain and Chai knew nothing.

681
00:41:35,333 --> 00:41:36,333
[Mek] Okay.

682
00:41:40,375 --> 00:41:42,000
- Let me ask you something.
- [Leh] Sure.

683
00:41:43,292 --> 00:41:45,125
Why are you taking the fall for Chai?

684
00:41:48,042 --> 00:41:49,792
Being on that damn boat… [clicks tongue]

685
00:41:51,042 --> 00:41:53,250
It's awful. I'd rather go to prison.

686
00:41:54,667 --> 00:41:56,417
[Mek] Is it really that bad on the boat?

687
00:41:57,625 --> 00:42:00,250
My missing fingers… You know the winch?

688
00:42:01,042 --> 00:42:02,208
The machine.

689
00:42:02,708 --> 00:42:03,958
On the boat.

690
00:42:04,833 --> 00:42:07,958
I had a long-sleeve shirt on,
and it got caught.

691
00:42:08,583 --> 00:42:10,500
It pulled me in. I couldn't pull away.

692
00:42:10,583 --> 00:42:12,125
So my fingers were torn off.

693
00:42:12,750 --> 00:42:16,750
When I couldn't work without my fingers,
the skipper still forced me to.

694
00:42:16,833 --> 00:42:18,792
He whipped my head with a stingray tail.

695
00:42:19,625 --> 00:42:22,750
Then he poured boiling water on my back
and had the crew stomp on me.

696
00:42:23,250 --> 00:42:25,208
All kinds of things happened on that boat.

697
00:42:25,292 --> 00:42:29,292
They treated me like I wasn't human.
Like I was a piece of trash.

698
00:42:29,375 --> 00:42:31,458
[brooding music playing]

699
00:42:31,542 --> 00:42:34,542
[Leh] And I still don't even know
when my dad will get off that boat.

700
00:42:36,458 --> 00:42:38,042
Your dad is on the boat too?

701
00:42:38,125 --> 00:42:39,917
[Leh] Yes, he's still there.

702
00:42:40,625 --> 00:42:42,500
When the skipper needed a scapegoat

703
00:42:42,583 --> 00:42:45,125
my dad groveled at his feet,

704
00:42:45,208 --> 00:42:46,958
begging him to pick me,

705
00:42:47,042 --> 00:42:50,083
knowing I couldn't survive
on the boat any longer.

706
00:42:50,167 --> 00:42:51,917
Missing fingers and unable to work.

707
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:55,167
Luckily, they didn't throw me overboard
to feed the fish.

708
00:42:57,125 --> 00:42:58,708
I think that's enough for today.

709
00:42:58,792 --> 00:42:59,833
[music fades]

710
00:43:00,583 --> 00:43:02,417
[Leh] There's a lot
of messed-up shit there.

711
00:43:02,500 --> 00:43:03,667
Shit happens every day.

712
00:43:05,250 --> 00:43:07,333
The other day was super weird.

713
00:43:07,417 --> 00:43:10,042
Out of nowhere, the skipper brought
a woman on board.

714
00:43:10,750 --> 00:43:12,125
Guess he was just horny.

715
00:43:12,792 --> 00:43:14,458
She was covered in bruises.

716
00:43:15,250 --> 00:43:17,708
Walking with a limp too.
No idea how he could sleep with her.

717
00:43:17,792 --> 00:43:20,167
- [chuckles]
- [soft tense music playing]

718
00:43:26,042 --> 00:43:27,542
Was it this woman?

719
00:43:32,500 --> 00:43:33,833
Hmm…

720
00:43:38,292 --> 00:43:39,667
Was it this woman?

721
00:43:39,750 --> 00:43:41,167
[music builds]

722
00:43:41,250 --> 00:43:42,417
[music fades]

723
00:43:43,750 --> 00:43:46,167
[intense music playing]

724
00:43:49,125 --> 00:43:52,458
[Kung] Are you crazy?
Go to the Criminal Court. Ugh.

725
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:57,250
I have new information.

726
00:43:57,792 --> 00:44:00,792
Leh told me that last week,
a woman was taken onto the boat.

727
00:44:00,875 --> 00:44:03,375
So I showed him Nay Oo's picture.
He said they look very similar.

728
00:44:03,458 --> 00:44:05,667
Most importantly, she's Burmese
and walked with a limp.

729
00:44:05,750 --> 00:44:09,042
If it's really Nay Oo,
I'll alert the authorities to save her.

730
00:44:09,125 --> 00:44:12,375
No. Stick to the plan.
And absolutely don't save her.

731
00:44:12,875 --> 00:44:16,292
How do you know? He might be lying,
or he just got the wrong person.

732
00:44:16,375 --> 00:44:18,417
But if it's possible,
shouldn't we at least try?

733
00:44:19,083 --> 00:44:21,792
You're Chai's lawyer
because you want him to confirm

734
00:44:21,875 --> 00:44:23,125
that Nay Oo exists, right?

735
00:44:23,750 --> 00:44:25,458
If that woman is Nay Oo, it's all over.

736
00:44:25,542 --> 00:44:27,458
We won't need Chai,
and Leh won't go to jail.

737
00:44:27,542 --> 00:44:29,417
- And my case would close.
- And if it's not her?

738
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:31,125
[music fades]

739
00:44:31,208 --> 00:44:33,667
There's nothing to lose.
We still save someone on the boat.

740
00:44:33,750 --> 00:44:34,750
Leh's dad is there too.

741
00:44:34,833 --> 00:44:36,708
[Jittri] How do you know
there's nothing to lose?

742
00:44:36,792 --> 00:44:39,750
If you raid Anan's boat recklessly,
he'll catch on.

743
00:44:39,833 --> 00:44:41,833
Then he'll pin the blame
on one of his men.

744
00:44:41,917 --> 00:44:43,542
And Anan will get away with it.

745
00:44:46,542 --> 00:44:47,667
[scoffs softly]

746
00:44:48,542 --> 00:44:51,000
So in the end, this has nothing
to do with my case, right?

747
00:44:51,083 --> 00:44:53,208
You just want to ruin Anan.
That's all you care about.

748
00:44:53,917 --> 00:44:56,417
What happens to me in the end
isn't even your damn problem.

749
00:44:57,833 --> 00:44:59,542
I know what Anan did to your parents.

750
00:44:59,625 --> 00:45:01,625
[suspenseful music playing]

751
00:45:05,500 --> 00:45:07,833
I mean, I get it if you want revenge.

752
00:45:07,917 --> 00:45:09,375
But this is my life.

753
00:45:10,167 --> 00:45:12,042
I'm not letting you use me as a pawn.

754
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:16,708
You think you're so much better than me
that you can judge me?

755
00:45:17,667 --> 00:45:19,000
How long has that woman been gone?

756
00:45:19,083 --> 00:45:21,250
Did you ever care
if she was dead or alive?

757
00:45:21,333 --> 00:45:22,750
No! You never did!

758
00:45:23,375 --> 00:45:25,292
You never really intended to help her.

759
00:45:26,208 --> 00:45:28,750
You just want her to go to prison
so you can walk free.

760
00:45:29,375 --> 00:45:31,667
If you say I used you as a pawn,
what about you?

761
00:45:31,750 --> 00:45:33,083
How are you any different?

762
00:45:38,333 --> 00:45:40,167
I'll bring that woman back

763
00:45:41,083 --> 00:45:43,708
and I won't let her spend
a single day in jail.

764
00:45:44,875 --> 00:45:47,792
So you'll see that we are nothing alike.

765
00:45:54,958 --> 00:45:56,958
[music concludes]

766
00:45:57,042 --> 00:45:58,958
[Ang] But be a little careful
with the white.

767
00:45:59,042 --> 00:46:02,250
I don't want it to be 100% white.
I prefer off-white.

768
00:46:02,333 --> 00:46:04,750
- [cell phone buzzing]
- Give me a second.

769
00:46:05,333 --> 00:46:08,333
[tense music playing]

770
00:46:08,417 --> 00:46:09,583
What's up?

771
00:46:09,667 --> 00:46:11,042
[Mek]<i> Hello, Ang. Listen.</i>

772
00:46:11,125 --> 00:46:13,833
I found a lead on Nay Oo.
Meet me at Chai's fishery right now.

773
00:46:14,500 --> 00:46:16,583
- [engine revving]
- [music intensifies]

774
00:46:24,250 --> 00:46:26,417
This island is the farthest we can go.

775
00:46:26,500 --> 00:46:28,833
Past this point,
we enter Cambodian waters.

776
00:46:28,917 --> 00:46:30,917
But from the info I have,

777
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:33,750
there's an island with a pier
just before crossing the border.

778
00:46:33,833 --> 00:46:35,333
I just don't know which one.

779
00:46:36,042 --> 00:46:38,042
Up ahead, there's an island

780
00:46:38,125 --> 00:46:40,250
where local fishermen go to fish.

781
00:46:40,792 --> 00:46:42,875
Then we better check them one by one.

782
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:45,042
- Okay.
- [officer] Got it.

783
00:46:45,125 --> 00:46:46,875
Captain, let's check one by one.

784
00:46:57,792 --> 00:46:59,167
- [Rern] Get up!
- [whip cracks]

785
00:47:00,542 --> 00:47:01,792
[Rern] What? Are you dying?

786
00:47:02,417 --> 00:47:03,708
I said, get up!

787
00:47:03,792 --> 00:47:05,208
- Get up!
- [worker groans]

788
00:47:05,292 --> 00:47:06,875
- [henchman 1] Skipper!
- Get up!

789
00:47:06,958 --> 00:47:08,042
Skipper!

790
00:47:08,917 --> 00:47:10,667
- The marine police are coming!
- [radio chirps]

791
00:47:10,750 --> 00:47:15,000
[henchman 2] <i>The police are moving in!</i>
<i>Lift the anchor and move!</i>

792
00:47:15,083 --> 00:47:16,375
[henchman 1] What do we do?

793
00:47:18,792 --> 00:47:21,958
- Tell them to hide below deck. Hurry!
- [henchman 1 in Burmese] Hey!

794
00:47:22,042 --> 00:47:23,917
- Get down!
- [Rern in Thai] I said, get up!

795
00:47:24,417 --> 00:47:25,417
Get the hell up!

796
00:47:25,500 --> 00:47:26,875
- I said, get up!
- [whip cracks]

797
00:47:26,958 --> 00:47:28,333
[music builds]

798
00:47:28,417 --> 00:47:29,625
- [music stops]
- [gun clicks]

799
00:47:29,708 --> 00:47:31,167
- [gunshots]
- [worker groans]

800
00:47:32,583 --> 00:47:33,792
Bastard!

801
00:47:34,500 --> 00:47:37,250
Get below deck! Hurry up! Move it!

802
00:47:37,333 --> 00:47:39,458
- Go!
- [intense music playing]

803
00:47:39,542 --> 00:47:40,583
Get below deck!

804
00:47:40,667 --> 00:47:43,417
- [man 1 in Burmese] Run!
- [in Thai] Move it! Get in there!

805
00:47:43,500 --> 00:47:45,292
[intense music continues]

806
00:47:55,083 --> 00:47:58,083
[officer 1] We've spotted the boat.
But no signs of life on board.

807
00:47:58,708 --> 00:47:59,958
That's very unlikely.

808
00:48:01,208 --> 00:48:02,250
[gunfire]

809
00:48:02,333 --> 00:48:04,083
- [officer 1] Everybody get down!
- [Pang yelps]

810
00:48:04,167 --> 00:48:05,542
- [music falls]
- [radio beeps]

811
00:48:05,625 --> 00:48:08,250
Dispatch, Dispatch!
Requesting V.7 backup. Over.

812
00:48:08,333 --> 00:48:10,042
I repeat, we are taking fire. Over.

813
00:48:10,125 --> 00:48:11,958
[dispatcher] <i>Reinforcements are en route.</i>

814
00:48:12,042 --> 00:48:13,458
- [radio beeps]
- Roger that. V.2, V.8.

815
00:48:13,542 --> 00:48:14,917
[tense music playing]

816
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:16,458
Captain, ease us in slowly.

817
00:48:16,542 --> 00:48:18,208
[gunfire continues]

818
00:48:24,958 --> 00:48:27,042
- [clock ticking]
- [music intensifies]

819
00:48:35,042 --> 00:48:36,750
[officer 1] Go, go, go, go!

820
00:48:39,833 --> 00:48:41,125
Please wait right here.

821
00:48:46,500 --> 00:48:47,792
[officer 2] Hey, freeze!

822
00:48:48,958 --> 00:48:49,958
Drop your weapon!

823
00:48:50,042 --> 00:48:51,583
- Drop your weapon!
- [officer 1] Drop it!

824
00:48:51,667 --> 00:48:53,583
Slowly! Kneel down!

825
00:48:54,833 --> 00:48:56,167
Check the top deck!

826
00:48:58,250 --> 00:48:59,333
[officer 3] Top deck clear!

827
00:48:59,917 --> 00:49:00,917
- Mek, wait!
- [Ang] Mek!

828
00:49:01,917 --> 00:49:02,833
Mek!

829
00:49:10,667 --> 00:49:13,083
Roger. Suspects are in custody. Over.
Roger that. V.2, V.8.

830
00:49:13,167 --> 00:49:15,542
- Sir, you shouldn't go in there.
- Excuse me. Sorry.

831
00:49:18,250 --> 00:49:20,833
[music fades]

832
00:49:24,333 --> 00:49:26,333
[suspenseful music playing]

833
00:49:27,792 --> 00:49:30,250
[music intensifies]

834
00:49:48,750 --> 00:49:50,083
[Ang retches, coughs]

835
00:50:01,583 --> 00:50:03,625
[music concludes]

836
00:50:04,375 --> 00:50:09,708
[water dripping]

837
00:50:11,333 --> 00:50:16,792
[boat creaking]

838
00:50:23,292 --> 00:50:29,792
[dripping and creaking continue]

839
00:50:37,708 --> 00:50:43,792
[waves crashing]

840
00:50:47,542 --> 00:50:50,625
[water continues dripping]

841
00:50:50,708 --> 00:50:55,000
[boat continues creaking]

842
00:50:57,000 --> 00:51:03,125
[chains jangling]

843
00:51:15,750 --> 00:51:21,625
[wind whistling]

844
00:51:30,125 --> 00:51:34,792
[waves crashing]

845
00:51:36,708 --> 00:51:42,208
[boat creaking]

846
00:52:02,783 --> 00:52:09,283
[water burbling]
